Perseid is the stunning Gulf Coast bistro inside Hotel Saint Augustine, led by acclaimed chef @aaronbludorn. The menu strikes the perfect balance between thoughtful and approachable—elevated flavors with a neighborhood feel.

They’re open for lunch daily from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m., making it a perfect spot for a relaxed midday bite in Montrose.

Don’t miss the Roasted Duck Breast—one of the best duck dishes I’ve ever had. Perfectly cooked, incredibly tender, juicy, and full of flavor.
📍: @perseidhtx inside @hotelsaintaugustine 4110 Loretto Drive, Houston TX 77006

#hotelsaintaugustine #houstonrestaurants #houstonhotels #houstoneats #houstonfood #perseidhtx

Sundays at the Houston Polo Club? 💖🐎

@tourshoustoncity 🚌 is a whole experience! I’ve lived here all my life and have never seen Downtown Houston like this. There is so much art, so many beautiful murals, and gorgeous green spaces.

The icing is Houston’s rich history told by a very entertaining tour guide! Sit back relax and enjoy the gorgeous views of Houston’s skyline. 
There’s also a super cute shop with snacks and treats, as well as fun souvenirs.

So tag your friends and be a tourist in your city! 

Follow me @neeneatshouston for more fun and food in Houston 🤘🏽

#houstoncitytours #tourhouston #beatourist #houstontx #mysecrethouston #downtownhouston #thingstodoinhouston #latinacontentcreator #neeneatshouston

✨ AAPI RESTAURANT WEEKS IN HOUSTON, TEXAS ✨ May is Asian American Pacific Islander month and Houston restaurants are spreading awareness by hosting AAPI Restaurant weeks. 🙌 By donating $15 to OCA greater Houston, you will get a passbook that will unlock special giveaways and discounts to participating restaurants. For every $15 donation, OCA Great Houston will donate a bag to rice to low income senior citizens. 🍚 *Portions of the donation will be put towards cost of staffing, logistics, and supporting OCA-Greater Houston’s youth and community programs. I’ll add the link to my bio if you’re interested! 😊

Info on the restaurants featured 👇 
📍 Ocean Crawfish // 8200 Wilcrest 
The crawfish here was sooo delicious. I love the citrus garlic butter 🤤 They also have various Vietnamese dishes and snacks like coconut snails, and wayyyy more snail options and seafood options. The fresh scallop was also fantastic!
📍 Saigon Food Street // Inside HK mall
They had lots of delicious Vietnamese dishes as well as drinks! There’s street food and even dishes that are completely new to me! Loved everything here as well. 
📍 Bui Quan An // Inside HK4
This spot is known for their bún bò Huế and the beef tail that they have in there. There’s also street snacks and even sugarcane drinks!
📍 Banh Cuon Hoa & Van Banh Mi // 11169 Beechnut St. 
These two are located right next to each other and since they’re owned by the same people, you can order whatever to either restaurants. They have rice rolls, hot stone bowl pho, and their banh mi are made fresh in house daily! Lots of y’all told me to try this banh mi spot and it did not disappoint. The bread was so fluffy and the crispy pork belly one was fantastic! 😋

HOUSTON STAYCATION SPOT YOU NEED TO KNOW ✨

If you're looking for a relaxing getaway without leaving the city, @themoranhotel is the move! This newly renovated hotel in @citycentrehou is perfect for a weekend staycation. Here’s why you’ll love it:

✨ Location, location, location – Steps away from 50+ shops and restaurants, it's in the heart of @citycentrehou , so there's always something to do.

🍸 On-site dining – Grab a craft cocktail at Allegory Bar or enjoy a cozy breakfast at Cafe Moran—both located right inside the hotel.

🛏️ Modern & comfy rooms – The renovations are stunning! Think chic decor, plush beds, and all the comfort you want from a luxe staycation.

latestPosts.caption:
Girls night done right at The Kennedy 🥂❤️

We spent the evening soaking in the timeless charm and upscale vibes of @thekennedyhouston a true gem tucked right in the heart of the city.🌆 From the moment we stepped in, we were swept away by the elegant ambiance, live piano, and warm hospitality that made the night feel extra special.🍸🏇

Okay but let’s talk about the food real quick… the lobster bisque🦞 was seriously so good, the Burger —perfection 🤩 And the homemade cookies at the end? Actually magical… plus our sweet waiter even brought us a glass of milk lol🍪✨

If you’re looking for a cute spot for girls night, date night, or just because —The Kennedy needs to be on your list!⚡️
